---
const steps = [
  {
    n: '01',
    t: 'Pick the wood',
    d: 'Cheaper plywood, multiplex birch, or solid hardwood like cherry — almost anything is possible. You tell me how you want your case to look, and we choose the material together.',
  },
  {
    n: '02',
    t: 'Cut and bond',
    d: 'Each panel is cut with a precision laser and glued together with a natural, solvent-free wood adhesive. We are constantly refining the process to push the quality higher with every build.',
  },
  {
    n: '03',
    t: 'Choose the finish',
    d: 'Natural, oiled, or stained — your call. Natural keeps the rawness of the wood, oil deepens the grain and protects it for decades, stain shifts the tone darker. None of them hide what the wood actually is.',
  },
];
---
<section id="craft" class="relative py-28 md:py-40 overflow-hidden bg-brand-walnut-dark">
  <img
    src="/images/detail.jpg"
    alt=""
    aria-hidden="true"
    class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover opacity-25 scale-110 blur-[2px]"
    loading="lazy"
  />
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-walnut-dark via-brand-walnut-dark/85 to-brand-walnut-dark"></div>

  <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-14 items-start">
      <div class="lg:col-span-5">
        <span class="text-brand-gold text-xs tracking-[0.32em] uppercase">How it's made</span>
        <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl mt-4 mb-8 leading-tight">
          Three steps.<br/>
          <span class="italic text-brand-gold">One pair of hands.</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-brand-cream/75 text-lg leading-relaxed font-light mb-5">
          No assembly line. No outsourced finishing. Every Timbrcase passes through the same workshop, the same eyes, twice — once before the finish, once before it's allowed to leave.
        </p>
        <p class="text-brand-cream/65 text-base leading-relaxed font-light mb-5">
          <span class="text-brand-gold">100 % made in Europe</span>, from European wood. The trees, the workshop, the hands — all on the same continent, all traceable.
        </p>
        <p class="text-brand-cream/65 text-base leading-relaxed font-light italic">
          Every case is a small piece of design art. Because each panel of wood has its own grain, its own flaws, its own light — no two Timbrcases will ever be exactly the same. Yours will only ever be yours.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-10 aspect-[16/9] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-brand-gold/10">
          <img src="/images/detail.jpg" alt="Multiplex birch lamination, close-up" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy"/>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:col-span-7 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {steps.map((s) => (
          <div class="border-t border-brand-gold/25 pt-6 pr-2">
            <div class="text-brand-gold/70 font-display text-sm mb-3">{s.n}</div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-2xl mb-3">{s.t}</h3>
            <p class="text-brand-cream/65 text-sm leading-relaxed font-light">{s.d}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
